-- Jones Apparel forecasts Q4 net loss of $2.48/shr
-- 
-- Mon Jan 29, 2007 5:40pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/29/businesspro-jonesapparel-outlook-dc-idUSWNAS881120070129

 

 (Reuters) - Jones Apparel Group Inc. ( JNY.N ) said it 
expects a fourth-quarter net loss of $2.48 a share and will 
take an after-tax, non-cash charge of about $322.2 million for 
the impairment of goodwill and trademarks. 


  The company forecast fourth-quarter adjusted earnings of 
about 51 cents a share, excluding certain charges, the shoe and 
clothing maker said in a statement.  (Reporting by Anant Vijay Kala in Bangalore)